nce, or charge</xsd:documentation></xsd:annotation><xsd:complexType><xsd:sequence><xsd:element name="D_248"><xsd:annotation><xsd:appinfo source="http://sap.com/xi/TextID">8d0b0ed11ff311e1889c0026b9aa16ff</xsd:appinfo><xsd:documentation>SAC01| Allowance or Charge Indicator. NOTES: If SAC01 is "A" or "C", then at least one of SAC05, SAC07, or SAC08 is required.</xsd:documentation></xsd:annotation><xsd:simpleType><xsd:restriction base="xsd:string"><xsd:length value="1"/></xsd:restriction></xsd:simpleType></xsd:element><xsd:element minOccurs="0" name="D_1300"><xsd:annotation><xsd:appinfo source="http://sap.com/xi/TextID">8d0b0ed21ff311e1c8370026b9aa16ff</xsd:appinfo><xsd:documentation>SAC02| Service, Promotion, Allowance, or Charge Code. NOTES: R0203 - At least one of SAC02 or SAC03 is required.</xsd:documentation></xsd:annotation><xsd:simpleType><xsd:restriction base="xsd:string"><xsd:length value="4"/></xsd:restriction></xsd:simpleType></xsd:element><xsd:element minOccurs="0" name="D_559"><xsd:annotation><xsd:appinfo source="http://sap.com/xi/TextID">8d0b0ed31ff311e1bb0b0026b9aa16ff</xsd:appinfo><xsd:documentation>SAC03| Agency Qualifier Code. NOTES: P0304 - If either SAC03 or SAC04 is present, then the other is required.</xsd:documentation></xsd:annotation><xsd:simpleType><xsd:restriction base="xsd:string"><xsd:length value="2"/></xsd:restriction></xsd:simpleType></xsd:element><xsd:element minOccurs="0" name="D_1301"><xsd:annotation><xsd:appinfo source="http://sap.com/xi/TextID">8d0b0ed41ff311e1a4d10026b9aa16ff</xsd:appinfo><xsd:documentation>SAC04| Agency Service, Promotion, Allowance, or Charge Code. NOTES: SAC04 may be used to uniquely identify the service, promotion, allowance, or charge. In addition, it may be used in conjunction to further the code in SAC02.</xsd:documentation></xsd:annotation><xsd:simpleType><xsd:restriction base="xsd:string"><xsd:minLength value="1"/><xsd:maxLength value="10"/></xsd:restriction></xsd:simpleType></xsd:element><xsd:element minO